# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# [body - explain WHAT changed and WHY, not HOW]
#
# Intent: <intent-type>
# Scope: <domain/module>[, <domain/module>]
# Decided-Against: <approach> (<reason>)
# Session: <YYYY-MM-DD>/<slug>
# Refs: <commit|issue|doc>[, ...]
# Context: <compact-json>
# Breaking: <description>
#
# --- Intent Vocabulary (choose exactly one) ---
# enable-capability  : New user-facing or system capability
# fix-defect         : Correcting incorrect behavior
# improve-quality    : Non-functional improvement (perf, readability)
# restructure        : Architectural change, module extraction
# configure-infra    : Tooling, CI/CD, dependencies, build system
# document           : Documentation, ADRs, comments, API docs
# explore            : Spike, prototype, hypothesis validation
# resolve-blocker    : Unblocking a dependent task or workflow
#
# --- Type Reference ---
# feat, fix, refactor, perf, docs, test, build, ci, chore, revert
#
# --- Rules ---
# Header: max 72 chars, imperative mood ("add" not "added")
# Body: wrap at 72-80 chars, explain what and why
# Trailers: blank line before trailers, Intent and Scope required
# Scope format: domain/module (e.g., auth/session, api/webhooks)
# Decided-Against: format as "approach (reason)" - highest-value trailer
#
# Install this template:
#   git config commit.template path/to/templates/.gitmessage
